{
  "texts": [
    "All hidden layers, except the last fully connected layer, are equipped with Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU) nonlinearity.",
    "The fusion network was trained by minimizing the cross-entropy loss L with l 1 regularization using backpropagation:h Ã ¼ arg min W X i;j Lðx i j þ z i j; y i j; WÞð2Þwhere x i j and z i j are the jth input vector from audio and video features, respectively, y j is the corresponding class label, and W is the set of network parameters, respectively.",
    "For the audio-video fusion model, we used initialization weights from the video classification model (see Algorithm 1).",
    "Empirically, the weights from the video model boost the convergence speed of the fusion model.",
    "DatasetsWe evaluated the MAiVAR on two popular action recognition datasets: UCF51 Takahashi et al [58] and Kinetics Sounds Arandjelovic and Zisserman [1].UCF51 is a subset of standard benchmark dataset UCF101 Soomro et al [55] for action recognition."
  ]
}